.planning/phases/57-measurement-telemetry-baseline/57-RESEARCH.md:317:- **Loading all JSONL for routine extraction:** JSONL files are large, unstable (streaming duplication, `/continue` inheritance), and not the primary data source for baselines. Use session-meta exclusively for Phase 57 routine operations. Signal: [sig-2026-03-02-claude-code-session-logs-large-unstable]
.planning/phases/57-measurement-telemetry-baseline/57-RESEARCH.md:321:- **Treating facets as ground truth:** Facets are AI-generated. `outcome` does NOT correlate with `tool_errors` (spk-005 finding). Do not draw conclusions based on single facets fields; use them as holistic indicators only. Always annotate facets-derived fields as AI estimates per TEL-05.
.planning/phases/57-measurement-telemetry-baseline/57-RESEARCH.md:366:**How to avoid:** Every facets-derived metric in baseline output must include explicit `n` (the facets-matched subset count, not total corpus count). TEL-05 also requires AI-estimate annotation. See stipulated constraint above.
