.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-02-22-debugger-git-add-a-bug-corrected.md:41:The original debugger spec predated the formal git safety convention (later consolidated in agent-protocol.md Section 1). The bug persisted because the debugger was a standalone spec with no cross-agent consistency checks. The extraction process served as an implicit audit — reading the git safety rules and then editing the agent created a natural context for catching the violation. This demonstrates a positive side effect of the shared-protocol extraction pattern: it forces cross-agent consistency review.
