.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-03-07-plan-checker-semantic-dimensions-systematic.md:42:verification: "{}"
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-03-07-plan-checker-semantic-dimensions-systematic.md:50:Phase 43 addressed a recurring plan checker capability gap pattern identified across three separate phases (34, 35, 42). Three independent signals (tool API assumptions, second-order effects, pre-execution review gaps) were systematically remediated by adding four new semantic validation dimensions to the plan checker. The plan checker was expanded from 7 structural dimensions to 11 (7 structural + 4 semantic), with each new dimension directly mapped to a specific identified gap.
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-03-07-plan-checker-semantic-dimensions-systematic.md:54:Phase 43, Plan 1 (Plan Intelligence & Templates). The plan checker is an LLM-based agent that validates plans before execution. It previously checked only structural correctness (task count, file lists, verification criteria). The semantic dimensions add validation for tool/API assumptions (Dim 8), configuration dependencies (Dim 9), directory/path assumptions (Dim 10), and signal reference accuracy (Dim 11).
