.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/sig-2026-04-10-phase-574-no-fix-chains-baseline.md:44:The git sensor scanned 300 commits (phase 57.4 branch + 200 commits of context) for consecutive `fix:`-prefixed commit chains of 3 or more. Zero such chains were found. Phase 57.4 itself contains exactly 1 fix-prefixed commit (`451afec5 fix(57.4-03)`), which is isolated — not part of any chain.
