.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/sig-2026-04-10-phase-574-no-fix-chains-baseline.md:61:2. **Phase risk profile.** Reference rewrites rarely produce test-failing code. The dominant risks for this phase were semantic (Q1 untested), authority-weighting, and workflow (subagent misroute) rather than code correctness. The fix-chain heuristic is poorly calibrated for semantic-risk phases.
