.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-04-09-socratic-flow-unverifiable-by-static-inspection.md:30:verification: {}
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-04-09-socratic-flow-unverifiable-by-static-inspection.md:40:Phase 57.1 was a telemetry extraction phase with exploratory deliberation elements. Artifact-based sensors can verify file outputs (declared files, verification results, commit structure) but cannot evaluate the quality of reasoning that occurred within a conversation session. Human verification was deferred but not formally tracked.
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-04-09-socratic-flow-unverifiable-by-static-inspection.md:44:The artifact sensor's scope is limited to persistent file artifacts. Conversational reasoning, deliberation quality, and Socratic exchange patterns leave no direct file trace (unless session logs are captured and analyzed). The log sensor is the natural complement for this gap, but it is currently a stub (see related epistemic-gap signal for log sensor).
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-03-05-plan01-task1-prior-session-commit.md:30:verification: "{}"
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-03-05-plan01-task1-prior-session-commit.md:46:Session interruption (context limit, user pause, or crash) during Plan 01 execution. The GSD executor handled the resume gracefully by detecting the existing commit. This may slightly understate the total execution duration since Task 1 work occurred in a separate session.
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-03-06-ci-test-regression-parse-inconclusive.md:30:verification: "{}"
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-03-06-ci-test-regression-parse-inconclusive.md:46:CI log output format may not include structured test count summaries that the sensor can reliably parse. Vitest output format or log truncation in GitHub Actions may prevent reliable extraction. This is a sensor capability limitation, not a CI issue.
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-03-26-tests-unit-install-test-js-modified-in-8.md:31:verification: "{}"
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-02-11-agent-inline-research-context-bloat.md:2:id: sig-2026-02-11-agent-inline-research-context-bloat
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-02-11-agent-inline-research-context-bloat.md:6:  - context-bloat
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-02-11-agent-inline-research-context-bloat.md:29:During a resume-work session, the agent read full Phase 13 RESEARCH.md (745 lines) and Phase 15 RESEARCH.md (744 lines) directly into the main conversation context, then ran 4 parallel web searches — all inline. This consumed ~1500+ lines of context for research that should have been delegated to a subagent (Explore or research agent) which would return a compact summary.
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-02-11-agent-inline-research-context-bloat.md:33:Post-v1.14 gap analysis discussion. User asked about Codex CLI's agent-spawning capabilities. Instead of spawning a research agent to investigate and return findings, the orchestrating agent loaded raw research files and web search results directly, bloating the main context window and reducing space for the actual design discussion.
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-02-11-agent-inline-research-context-bloat.md:37:Agent defaulted to direct file reads and web searches for "quick" lookups without considering cumulative context cost. The 1500+ lines of research files were not "quick" — they should have triggered the heuristic to delegate to a subagent. Convention needed: research tasks exceeding ~200 lines of source material should be delegated, not inlined.
.planning/knowledge/signals/sig-2026-04-09-shared-reference-doc-convergence-pattern.md:19:Phase 57.2 created `get-shit-done/references/claim-types.md` as a single shared ontology consumed by 3 downstream agents (discuss-phase, researcher, context-checker) via explicit path references. All 5 wiring points were verified as connected.
.planning/knowledge/signals/sig-2026-04-09-shared-reference-doc-convergence-pattern.md:23:When multiple agents need a shared vocabulary (here: 7 claim types + 3 verification levels), having each agent define its own version leads to drift. A single reference doc with explicit `@get-shit-done/references/claim-types.md` path references creates a convergence point that agents read at runtime.
.planning/knowledge/signals/sig-2026-04-09-shared-reference-doc-convergence-pattern.md:27:- `claim-types.md` referenced in discuss-phase.md (12 references), gsdr-context-checker.md (upstream_input), gsd-phase-researcher.md (upstream_input)
.planning/knowledge/signals/sig-2026-04-09-shared-reference-doc-convergence-pattern.md:33:- Depends on agents actually reading the referenced file at runtime — if path resolution fails or context window exhausted, drift can still occur
.planning/knowledge/signals/get-shit-done-reflect/2026-03-01-zero-deviation-execution-phase-33.md:43:verification: "{}"
